The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Dec. 23: Six leading bankers, including ICICI Securities and Kotak Mahindra, are understood to have been shortlisted for managing the estimated Rs 14,000-crore divestment programme of NMDC, banking sources said. Seventeen investment bankers had made presentations for advising the government on the follow-on-public offer of NMDC.                            
	 Mumbai, Dec. 23: The Bank of India is set to become the latest entrant in the home loan rate war, after biggies such as the SBI and HDFC, by offering 8 per cent fixed rate for the first two years for loans up to Rs 30 lakh.                             
	 New York, Dec. 23: The US car maker Ford Motor has agreed to all substantiative commercial terms related to the planned sale of Volvo Car Corp to Chinese auto-maker Zhejiang Geely Holding.                            
	 Calcutta, Dec. 23: Adhunik Metaliks has signed definitive agreements with India Infrastructure Fund for the investment of Rs 250 crore in its power subsidiary Adhunik Power amp; Natural Resources.                                                                                                                          
